From sidb at google.com  Sat Apr 25 00:02:38 2015
From: sidb at google.com (Siddhartha Bagaria)
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2015 22:02:38 +0000
Subject: [Bioc-devel] Announcing a new package: GoogleGenomics
In-Reply-To: <CAACA9LNkSeUM_id5GkE08Jy6m1zoe=xQYyE1wcqG82PzB9bTbQ@mail.gmail.com>
References: <CAACA9LNkSeUM_id5GkE08Jy6m1zoe=xQYyE1wcqG82PzB9bTbQ@mail.gmail.com>
Message-ID: <CAACA9LP+RHZjGnYOE+h9Z7DhwO4UBaeAT6jQL-9Uayw5cxjbiQ@mail.gmail.com>

Hi everyone,

I am happy to announce the availability of the GoogleGenomics
<http://bioconductor.org/packages/devel/bioc/html/GoogleGenomics.html> package
in the latest release and devel branches of Bioconductor.

This package is meant to be the R/Bioconductor interface to the Google
Genomics API <https://cloud.google.com/genomics/>. At present, the package
implements very simple read-only interfaces to reads and variants data for
public genomics datasets and any private datasets you might have uploaded
through the API.

We would love to have feature requests from users on what we should
prioritize while completing the implementation for all API methods. Any
other feedback is more than welcome.

Please use https://github.com/googlegenomics/api-client-r/issues to file
feature requests or general feedback. There is also a discussion on
near-term future roadmap on
https://github.com/googlegenomics/api-client-r/pull/37#issuecomment-94896723
.

Thank you.

Best regards,
Siddhartha Bagaria

